modules.description: Compares two values for equality and generates a hash value for a given instance. It operates on a single abstract type `t` used to represent build configurations. This is utilized to ensure consistent handling of build settings in dependency resolution and caching mechanisms.

Provides operations for creating, merging, and querying sets using hash table implementations. Works with unordered collections of unique elements, supporting membership checks and set algebra. Used to efficiently manage dynamic data collections where fast lookups and updates are required.

Provides operations to create, modify, and query a set of elements, including adding, removing, and checking membership. Works with a custom element type and a set abstract type, supporting iteration and folding over elements. Used to efficiently manage unique collections, such as tracking visited nodes in graph algorithms or deduplicating input data.
